    <item>
      <title>Why My Eyes Gently Roll</title>
      <link>https://ashfurrow.com/blog/why-my-eyes-gently-roll/</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Last week, an article from the Washington Post titled &lt;a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2017/lifestyle/the-slow-secret-death-of-the-electric-guitar/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Why my guitar gently weeps&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; made its way around the internet&amp;rsquo;s various music circles. The article makes some noise about falling guitar sales and draws conclusions from interviews that the author conducted with various captains of industry; its thesis is that sales are trending down, the industry is shrinking, and a lack of &amp;ldquo;guitar heroes&amp;rdquo; is to blame. Young people – apparently – just don&amp;rsquo;t have enough rock stars to look up to and emulate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you decide to read the post (it&amp;rsquo;s not long) prepare yourself for some extreme eye-rolling. Also, the article uses some weird JavaScript scroll hijacking, so have fun.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Almost as an aside, the article mentions a shift towards more women and girls learning guitar, but brushes their increased interest aside as trivial – or based purely in aesthetics. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andy Mooney, the Fender CEO, calls [Taylor] Swift “the most influential guitarist of recent years.”&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“I don’t think that young girls looked at Taylor and said, ‘I’m really impressed by the way she plays G major arpeggios.’ ” Mooney says. “They liked how she looked, and they wanted to emulate her.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This sounds dismissive. After all, young folks of the past were focused &lt;em&gt;only&lt;/em&gt; on the sounds of musicians and not their looks (for example, this is why KISS is known for wearing only dull boring outfits during performances). Girls don&amp;rsquo;t care about music, just about looks. Uh huh.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From a writing perspective, the biggest weakness of the article is that the author neglected to include perspectives from actual &lt;em&gt;guitarists&lt;/em&gt;. Instead, Geoff Edgars tacitly implies that falling guitar sales = declining industry = declining guitar popularity. A lot of folks around guitar forums and YouTube have pointed out this fallacy, and they further refute the claim that there are no &amp;ldquo;guitar heroes&amp;rdquo; by offering their own list of popular players. Usually men. Actually, all men.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I&amp;rsquo;m starting to think that just maybe our society has some kind of problem with attitudes towards women.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree with the musicians&amp;rsquo; rebuttal, that there &lt;em&gt;are&lt;/em&gt; still &amp;ldquo;guitar heroes&amp;rdquo; (gosh I dislike that term). I can name a few bands that really influenced my decision to pick up the guitar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, there&amp;rsquo;s such an abundance of educational resources on learning guitar that, since starting in December, I&amp;rsquo;ve at times felt overwhelmed by just how much there is to learn, and just how many ways there are to learn it all. I would be interested in reading an article discussing these resources, the rising popularity of YouTube as a music education platform, and hearing from a variety of musicians (of all genders) about their perspectives on the guitar industry&amp;rsquo;s decline. But that would require the Washington Post to investigate – which is apparently too much to ask.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 18:16:47 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ashfurrow.com/blog/why-my-eyes-gently-roll/</guid>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Feelings are Hard</title>
      <link>https://ashfurrow.com/blog/feelings-are-hard/</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Things have been getting to me lately. Big things, little things, all kinds of things. The result is: I get upset. Angry even.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Aaaaaand because I insist on spending so much of my life on Twitter (I need to stop that&amp;hellip;) everyone gets to see me get upset at things. The latest problems in my life are bringing the wrong computer cable and the LEGO store being sold out of something I want. Pretty childish stuff.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="en"&gt;&lt;p lang="en" dir="ltr"&gt;Hey Ash, sounds like you’re not having the best day. Here’s a box of fucking adorable goddamn kittens. It’ll help you on your way. &lt;a href="https://t.co/92nzKdfbFB"&gt;pic.twitter.com/92nzKdfbFB&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Aaron Vegh 📎 (@aaronvegh) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/aaronvegh/status/875051392515403784"&gt;June 14, 2017&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt; &lt;script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See, things were going great until about six weeks ago when my doctor suggested going off one of my medications. I&amp;rsquo;m on a very small dose, and we wanted to see if I needed it. Turns out I desperately do. Within a week I was miserable, flat, depressed. I finally got back on the medication, and as soon as it kicked in, I caught a cold. So I&amp;rsquo;m back to feeling miserable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Playing guitar can help, except my wrists hurt too much to play. So I get a little more sad. Sleeping helps, I feel better in the mornings. Doing things helps, so I feel better when I make it to the office.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the sort of back drop for this emotional rollercoaster is the political landscape of 2017. What a shitty year it&amp;rsquo;s been and promises to continue to be.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s going to be okay – I have a supportive partner, and a therapist, and a psychiatrist. And I&amp;rsquo;m making progress all the time. I&amp;rsquo;ve just had such a hard time over the past month or so. This summer was supposed to be refreshing and exciting, but instead it&amp;rsquo;s began with familiar ennui. Things are looking up, I guess, but I can&amp;rsquo;t help feel like I&amp;rsquo;m going to be stuck here forever.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 14 Jun 2017 18:12:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ashfurrow.com/blog/feelings-are-hard/</guid>
    </item>
